diff --git a/CHANGES.rst b/CHANGES.rst
index 2db769f..f75c01f 100644
--- a/CHANGES.rst
+++ b/CHANGES.rst
@@ -62,6 +62,13 @@ Unreleased
 -   Contexts created during shell completion are closed properly, fixing
     ``ResourceWarning``s when using ``click.File``. :issue:`2644` :pr:`2800`
     :pr:`2767`
+-   ``click.edit()``'s ``filename`` argument can be a single filename or an
+    iterable of filenames, allowing multiple files to be edited at once in
+    editors that support it.
+-   Add a ``process_priority`` parameter to ``click.edit()`` to optionally
+    set the CPU priority of the launched editor process. Unsupported or
+    failed priority changes are ignored rather than causing the edit to
+    fail.
 
 
 Version 8.1.8
